<TITLE> 3 killed in Rupganj road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, Dec 25 (bdnews24.com)--Three people were killed and 15 others injured at Adhuria in Rupganj on Friday when a bus and a truck collided. Two of the deceased were identified as 'Siddiqur', 45, and 'Shahjahan', 35, while the third could not be immediately named. Three among the injured, in critical condition, were taken to Dhaka Medical College and Hospital while others were admitted to other hospitals. Officer in charge of Rupganj Police Station Forkan Sikder told bdnews24.com the accident took place at 8:45am when a Kanchpur-bound bus drove into an oncoming truck. The bus was smashed and the three were killed on the spot. Bodies have been handed over to the relatives. Preparation for filing a case is underway, the officer added. bdne
